_decoded_content.name: Smart Hands
_decoded_content.description:
Update:- Uploaded files but forgot to short the name of the files but you may get some hints in the last name of the files.
Note: it's still a work in progress and I have not yet made any assembly guide for more detail you can refer to the fusion file for assembly.


Above given are some of the picture of my final year project which is a multi-purpose Smart hands i.e it can acts as a telepresence Arm with a wear on controller or can be used as a Prosthetic Arm also can be used as a model.
I am just uploading the picture coz I am not sure if the design is good and if someone needs the design but it was one of my 1st advanced level CAD designs which were done on Autodesk Fusion 360. I have spent more then 400 hours in designing this arm for one of my friend as a prosthetic arm and spend more then 1 week in printing and joining things together this design was inspired by 2 fabulous products which was Exiii Handiii(http://exiii.jp/) and Dexmo (http://www.dextarobotics.com/) though it does not look so good but still i think it has a very great modular look.
I am also not sure about how should i publish files if open source or should charge for the files.
If you like the pictures and would like to talk just drop a comment.
hope you have a great day :)
